1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,680
(THUNDER CRASHING)

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:19,640
(WHOOSHING)

3
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:28,600
(WHOOSHING)

4
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:38,400
-The dress is a little daring.
-Yep, so I went for this instead.

5
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:41,000
-Are we going out?
-Parents are asleep.

6
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:43,360
How's Storm Cage?

7
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:46,240
I'm on the first night of 12,000
consecutive life sentences.

8
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:48,320
Kind of early to say.
Where are we going?

9
00:00:48,680 --> 00:00:51,120
Alderin Beta. Boring,
planet of the chip shops.

10
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:54,040
But there is a 400-foot tree
growing out of a clifftop

11
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:56,400
on the north side of a mountain
in the middle of the sea.

12
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:58,520
And if you take the lift to the top
and look up,

13
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:01,840
at exactly 12 minutes past midnight
on the 21st of September, 2360,

14
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:04,440
you can see more stars in one sky
that at any other moment

15
00:01:04,520 --> 00:01:07,640
in the history of the universe.
It's like daylight, only magic.

16
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,080
You could read a book by it.

17
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:13,640
-Whoo!
-Is it okay if I don't?

18
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:15,520
-(WHOOSHING)
-We've got 10 minutes. Get dressed.

19
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,400
Oh, that's so close
to the perfect sentence.

20
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:18,480
Hmm.

21
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:21,040
-Did you bring the diary?
-It's a diary?

22
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:24,640
It is now, because River,
from now on, there are rules.

23
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:26,560
Ooh, you've gone all strict.
Not that I mind.

24
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:28,440
River, you and I,
it's all in the wrong order.

25
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:29,520
We never meet in sequence.

26
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:31,760
You put everything in the diary
so we know where we are.

27
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:34,000
Put what in the diary? Sweetie,
I'm in the highest security prison

28
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:35,280
in all of the known universe.

29
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:38,080
River Song could walk in and out of
the prison like the walls aren't there.

30
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:39,400
-I'm River Song.
-Then you'll be fine.

31
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:41,520
If you don't like the dress,
there's plenty more in the wardrobe.

32
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:43,800
First right, second left,
just past the helter-skelter.

33
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:50,120
(LASER GUNS FIRING)

34
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:57,200
-River!
-I knew you'd come back here,

35
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:58,480
you nostalgic idiot.

36
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:00,280
-Hold me!
-River! River!

37
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:01,760
River!

38
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:02,920
River?

